Try the stone bowl bibimbap, it's incredible. Also, excellent sushi, as well as a varied sake selection.

Hidden Gem alert! This place is great - very quaint, nestled on Moody Street near Queens Cleaners (a few places down). What makes this place really distinct is the Sushi Chef; he comes from one of the top sushi restaurants in the Copley area, and has the know how that you'll be able to see (and taste). I'll just ask him to put a plate together of what he thinks is best, and I've never been disappointed. Definitely a place for Sushi connoisseurs - but at a much more affordable level. Check it out!
Great food! Service was excellent too!
Chef John is awesome. Very clean and attentive staff. Sushi is the highlight.

Spectacular service and really nice food.  Seems like mostly standard staples to Japanese and Korean foods. I'm pretty sure the very friendly lady that seated and served us is an owner and it shows. Honestly I'm part Korean and in touch with my Korean family and these are the nicest Korean people I've ever met.

First time eating here... and eating Korean food in general. The staff was friendly and warm. We did not order an appetizer, but we were served 4 small dishes of various sides before our miso soup came out. It was fun to try the different items. My wife ordered the dolsot bibimbap, and I ordered the spicy pork bulgogi. One of the staff saw my wife struggling with how to eat bibimbap and politely asked if it was our first time and it she could show us how to eat it. The food was delicious. We will definitely be returning.
This is my go to place for sushi in the area.

Overall great food and services, price is reasonable.  I am here for the Bibimbap and I am very satisfied. They are authentic, the side dishes they provide are the best part.  Although this is a Japanese restaurant, I am glad to see they are adding new dishes like chilly pot and spicy hot pot, which I have been long for in U.S. And I am definitely not disappointed after trying them out.
Great quality of food
Delicious sushi 🍣 However when we ordered the goldfish sushi, there were some small bones in the meat. Otherwise was very flavorful.

Highly recommend Ponzu.  We're regulars there. I love their Hwe Dup Bab and their kimchi jiigae is the best in the area.  They have a good beef tataki appetizer.  If you're feeling adventurous and you would be comfortable with beef tartare, they serve the Korean analog called Yuk Hwe.  It's a rare treat in outside of Korea, and Ponzu's is exception.  They also have a complete sushi bar and a variety of other Japanese and Korean entrees.  The owners are extremely friendly and the space is well maintained.  The service is excellent.  They earned me five star rating and I've been to probably 80 or 90% of the Korean restaurant in the greater Boston area.

Nice cozy family owned business. Where you will find the owner pouring water and making sure everybody is doing fine. Have a great time after work with a broad selection of sushi and don't forget to have mochi before you go. 👍🏽
Amazing food and service!
Good food our waitress was kind

Very good dumpling soup and sushi! Also great service, but let's talk about the food.  The dumpling soup was more than a few dumplings in broth. It included pieces of the dough as well as other pieces of vegetables, so it wasn't just plain. And the dumplings also tasted good, let's not forget about those.  The sushi was also great and appeared to be freshly made. We could see it being made behind the counter, and even with a few other tables it still was prepared and served quickly. And it didn't even taste like poor quality, cheap sushi that you often find around here.  The service was also fantastic. There are only a few tables so they were able to keep on top of everything.

Biggest ripped off in the whole Moody street.  So I ordered Mala pot take out and was waiting there for almost an hour. During my waiting no check up was given and I guess they just don’t care.  My Malapot cost $59.92, and it turned out it is THE BIGGEST RIPPED OFF in the whole Moody street. One example is the beef tender that costs $6 - 5 tiny pieces and smaller than a tennis ball.  I’m not going anymore and I am issuing a dispute from my bank.  Ratings way down!

very displeased. the miso soup does not taste japanese. it tastes more like a thai or korean style soup. the sushi itself is extremely chewy and not fresh tasting. very disappointed.

Fantastic and fresh Sushi, a good chunk of the menu is super authentic and is great for hardcore sushi and Korean food fans like myself, while a decent section is available to normies who prefer California Rolls, since they need love to. I especially loved the uni, the ikura, the sushi boat, the soondoobu chigae and the wide selection of nigiri!  The mouth watering real Korean food at this hidden gem is a refreshing change especially since Massachusetts does not have a lot of decent authentic Korean restaurants compared to LA or Atlanta, so this is my new go to! Also the sushi chef and wait staff are super chill, polite and sweet.  If you want the real stuff we Asians eat and not just another fried rice and egg roll joint, this place is for you. If not, you should still try it because holy cow it's still some of the best you'll find this far North.

I highly recommend the place and don't be too shy to ask for a place next to tbe window

Great sushi menu with some interesting combinations.  Decent sized restaurant and bar, although a little tight as the front section is stuffed with ~six two person tables. Prior to entrees, a selection of five small appetizer style dishes are presented. Pickled carrots, some sort of potato dish, pickled sprouts?, broccoli, and kimchi; all very good, and totally unexpected. We ordered Crab Rangoon and never received them, so accepted these dishes as our appetizer instead.  For sushi rolls we ordered Goldfish Maki, Angus Beef Tempura Maki, Gold Finger Maki, and Dragon Maki. The Angus Beef Tampura Maki was the standout for the evening, being a VERY different roll from anything I've ever had before. All four rolls were very good and fairly priced compared to other sushi restaurants.
